<h2>Before You File</h2>

<h3>✅ Checklist: Have you completed these steps?</h3>

<ul>
  <li>☐ <strong>Sent a Letter Before Claim</strong> to the defendant at least 30 days ago</li>
  <li>☐ <strong>Enclosed the Information Sheet and Reply Form</strong> with the Letter Before Claim</li>
  <li>☐ <strong>Waited 30 days</strong> for the defendant to respond or pay</li>
  <li>☐ <strong>Considered any response or payment offer</strong> from the defendant</li>
  <li>☐ <strong>Gathered all supporting evidence</strong> (tenancy agreement, rent ledger, bank statements, photos)</li>
  <li>☐ <strong>Calculated interest correctly</strong> (see Interest Calculation sheet)</li>
</ul>

<p>
<strong>⚠️ IMPORTANT:</strong> If you have not sent a Letter Before Claim and waited 30 days, you <strong>must do this first</strong>. The court may penalize you in costs if you do not follow the Pre-Action Protocol.
</p>

